  "interop_compat_risks": "The risk is that container-names set in shadow trees may now match as flat tree ancestor container for outer tree elements which are slotted into the shadow tree, or for ::part rules targeting elements inside the shadow tree which additionally rely on @container queries in outer tree rules.\n\nM142 introduced a use counter along with the implementation for detecting such cases in the wild:\n\nhttps://chromestatus.com/metrics/feature/timeline/popularity/5659\n\nThree sites reported back:\n\nhttps://redhatofficial.github.io/:\n\nSets padding which is overridden by another declaration not affected by container queries. No change.\n\nhttps://www.redhat.com/:\n\nSets padding to 0, which is also the initial value. No change.\n\nhttps://www.kansascityfed.org/:\n\nNot able to trigger loading or navigating around this site.\n\n\nFirefox has always shipped this behavior without noticing any interop issues according to the discussion in https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/12090#issuecomment-3204775586\n",
